<br>
It tried to be technically accurate (as was the earlier film, Destination Moon)<br>
<br>
It progressed, episode by episode, in chronological fashion.<br>
<br>
First trips to orbit. Then constructing a space station.<br>
<br>
The landing on the Moon, followed by building the first primitive lunar base, etc<br>
<br>
GREAT STUFF!<br>
<br>
In my favorite episode, a group of stranded astronauts must hike a long way back to shelter. Unfortunately, their air supply won't suffice for the time required. They salvaged a large oxygen tank which would supply them with enough air. The tank had a special valve to connect it to the suits.<br>
 The required wrench for the valve was luckily in the possession of one of the astronauts. Unfortunately it was in his SHIRT POCKET, inside his spacesuit.<br>
<br>
Loved that show!<br>
<br>
yale<br>
